==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entoperipheral
<hw>En`to*pe*riph"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ento-</ets> + <ets>peripheral</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Being, or having its origin, within the
external surface of the body; -- especially applied to feelings, such as
hunger, produced by internal disturbances. Opposed to
<contr>epiperipheral</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entophyte</ent>⟦br⟧
